      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Description copied from class: Node
        Compares the specified object with this Node for equality. Note that this should not be implemented as a reference == comparison, but as a data comparison. Other things to keep in mind are that, because nodes are used as map keys, all the attributes used in the comparison between nodes must not change during the live of the object, so they should be declared final.
        Specified by:
        equals in class Node
        Parameters:
        o - object to compare with this.
        Returns:
        true if o is a instance of Node, it's not null and is equal to this node.
